<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The error messages
  INI_SIZE:  File '%value%' exceeds the defined ini size
  FORM_SIZE: File '%value%' exceeds the defined form size
doesn't tells the value of size.
The message is useless for the user uploading a file.</p>

<p>Expected Messages:
  INI_SIZE:  File '%value%' exceeds the defined ini size of %iniSize%   : File 'foo.bar' exceeds the defined ini size of 1 Mb
  FORM_SIZE: File '%value%' exceeds the defined form size of %formSize% : File 'foo.bar' exceeds the defined form size of 512 Kb
-&gt; It would be the best if the size gets displayed as a "normalized" value but if it will be displayed as real bytes only it's ok, too.</p>

